{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":378,"text":"I have a question:"},{"time":2271,"text":"Who here remembers when they first realized"},{"time":5648,"text":"they were going to die?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9071,"text":"I do. I was a young boy,"},{"time":11573,"text":"and my grandfather had just died,"},{"time":14628,"text":"and I remember a few days later lying in bed at night"},{"time":18546,"text":"trying to make sense of what had happened."},{"time":22180,"text":"What did it mean that he was dead?"},{"time":24815,"text":"Where had he gone?"},{"time":26599,"text":"It was like a hole in reality had opened up"},{"time":30021,"text":"and swallowed him."},{"time":32156,"text":"But then the really shocking\nquestion occurred to me:"},{"time":34958,"text":"If he could die, could it happen to me too?"},{"time":38448,"text":"Could that hole in reality open up and swallow me?"},{"time":41747,"text":"Would it open up beneath my bed"},{"time":43537,"text":"and swallow me as I slept?"},{"time":46771,"text":"Well, at some point, all children\nbecome aware of death."},{"time":50959,"text":"It can happen in different ways, of course,"},{"time":52864,"text":"and usually comes in stages."},{"time":54697,"text":"Our idea of death develops as we grow older."},{"time":58210,"text":"And if you reach back into the dark corners"},{"time":60939,"text":"of your memory,"},{"time":62636,"text":"you might remember something like what I felt"},{"time":65639,"text":"when my grandfather died and when I realized"},{"time":68894,"text":"it could happen to me too,"},{"time":70844,"text":"that sense that behind all of this"},{"time":73423,"text":"the void is waiting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76760,"text":"And this development in childhood"},{"time":79037,"text":"reflects the development of our species."},{"time":81858,"text":"Just as there was a point in your development"},{"time":85173,"text":"as a child when your sense of self and of time"},{"time":88699,"text":"became sophisticated enough"},{"time":90798,"text":"for you to realize you were mortal,"},{"time":94720,"text":"so at some point in the evolution of our species,"},{"time":98426,"text":"some early human's sense of self and of time"},{"time":101441,"text":"became sophisticated enough"},{"time":103684,"text":"for them to become the first human to realize,"},{"time":106799,"text":"\"I'm going to die.\""},{"time":110232,"text":"This is, if you like, our curse."},{"time":112451,"text":"It's the price we pay for being so damn clever."},{"time":116494,"text":"We have to live in the knowledge"},{"time":118593,"text":"that the worst thing that can possibly happen"},{"time":121254,"text":"one day surely will,"},{"time":122878,"text":"the end of all our projects,"},{"time":124384,"text":"our hopes, our dreams, of our individual world."},{"time":127848,"text":"We each live in the shadow of a personal"},{"time":131029,"text":"apocalypse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133018,"text":"And that's frightening. It's terrifying."},{"time":135522,"text":"And so we look for a way out."},{"time":137982,"text":"And in my case, as I was about five years old,"},{"time":141263,"text":"this meant asking my mum."},{"time":144258,"text":"Now when I first started asking"},{"time":146720,"text":"what happens when we die,"},{"time":148501,"text":"the grown-ups around me at the time"},{"time":150593,"text":"answered with a typical English mix of awkwardness"},{"time":153796,"text":"and half-hearted Christianity,"},{"time":156783,"text":"and the phrase I heard most often"},{"time":158727,"text":"was that granddad was now"},{"time":160286,"text":"\"up there looking down on us,\""},{"time":162750,"text":"and if I should die too, which\nwouldn't happen of course,"},{"time":165715,"text":"then I too would go up there,"},{"time":168511,"text":"which made death sound a lot like"},{"time":170561,"text":"an existential elevator."},{"time":173215,"text":"Now this didn't sound very plausible."},{"time":176333,"text":"I used to watch a children's\nnews program at the time,"},{"time":179236,"text":"and this was the era of space exploration."},{"time":181676,"text":"There were always rockets going up into the sky,"},{"time":183850,"text":"up into space, going up there."},{"time":186546,"text":"But none of the astronauts when they came back"},{"time":188875,"text":"ever mentioned having met my granddad"},{"time":192107,"text":"or any other dead people."},{"time":194566,"text":"But I was scared,"},{"time":195869,"text":"and the idea of taking the existential elevator"},{"time":198309,"text":"to see my granddad"},{"time":199915,"text":"sounded a lot better than being swallowed"},{"time":201330,"text":"by the void while I slept."},{"time":204401,"text":"And so I believed it anyway,"},{"time":206670,"text":"even though it didn't make much sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209341,"text":"And this thought process that I went through"},{"time":211583,"text":"as a child, and have been through many times since,"},{"time":214114,"text":"including as a grown-up,"},{"time":216024,"text":"is a product of what psychologists call"},{"time":218471,"text":"a bias."},{"time":219935,"text":"Now a bias is a way in which we systematically"},{"time":223209,"text":"get things wrong,"},{"time":224927,"text":"ways in which we miscalculate, misjudge,"},{"time":227611,"text":"distort reality, or see what we want to see,"},{"time":231200,"text":"and the bias I'm talking about"},{"time":233432,"text":"works like this:"},{"time":234870,"text":"Confront someone with the fact"},{"time":237105,"text":"that they are going to die"},{"time":238652,"text":"and they will believe just about any story"},{"time":241685,"text":"that tells them it isn't true"},{"time":243543,"text":"and they can, instead, live forever,"},{"time":245957,"text":"even if it means taking the existential elevator."},{"time":250042,"text":"Now we can see this as the biggest bias of all."},{"time":254470,"text":"It has been demonstrated in over 400"},{"time":257345,"text":"empirical studies."},{"time":259026,"text":"Now these studies are ingenious, but they're simple."},{"time":261535,"text":"They work like this."},{"time":263470,"text":"You take two groups of people"},{"time":264960,"text":"who are similar in all relevant respects,"},{"time":267743,"text":"and you remind one group that they're going to die"},{"time":270432,"text":"but not the other, then you compare their behavior."},{"time":273061,"text":"So you're observing how it biases behavior"},{"time":276934,"text":"when people become aware of their mortality."},{"time":280688,"text":"And every time, you get the same result:"},{"time":283600,"text":"People who are made aware of their mortality"},{"time":286687,"text":"are more willing to believe stories"},{"time":288698,"text":"that tell them they can escape death"},{"time":290561,"text":"and live forever."},{"time":292333,"text":"So here's an example: One recent study"},{"time":294622,"text":"took two groups of agnostics,"},{"time":297392,"text":"that is people who are undecided"},{"time":298988,"text":"in their religious beliefs."},{"time":301503,"text":"Now, one group was asked to think about being dead."},{"time":305087,"text":"The other group was asked to think about"},{"time":306732,"text":"being lonely."},{"time":308565,"text":"They were then asked again\nabout their religious beliefs."},{"time":311381,"text":"Those who had been asked\nto think about being dead"},{"time":314245,"text":"were afterwards twice as likely to express faith"},{"time":317818,"text":"in God and Jesus."},{"time":319478,"text":"Twice as likely."},{"time":321256,"text":"Even though the before they\nwere all equally agnostic."},{"time":323964,"text":"But put the fear of death in them,"},{"time":325725,"text":"and they run to Jesus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329584,"text":"Now, this shows that reminding people of death"},{"time":333111,"text":"biases them to believe, regardless of the evidence,"},{"time":336341,"text":"and it works not just for religion,"},{"time":338366,"text":"but for any kind of belief system"},{"time":340603,"text":"that promises immortality in some form,"},{"time":344063,"text":"whether it's becoming famous"},{"time":345868,"text":"or having children"},{"time":347282,"text":"or even nationalism,"},{"time":348629,"text":"which promises you can live\non as part of a greater whole."},{"time":351902,"text":"This is a bias that has shaped"},{"time":353833,"text":"the course of human history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357172,"text":"Now, the theory behind this bias"},{"time":359439,"text":"in the over 400 studies"},{"time":361176,"text":"is called terror management theory,"},{"time":363305,"text":"and the idea is simple. It's just this."},{"time":365655,"text":"We develop our worldviews,"},{"time":368204,"text":"that is, the stories we tell ourselves"},{"time":370361,"text":"about the world and our place in it,"},{"time":373097,"text":"in order to help us manage"},{"time":375379,"text":"the terror of death."},{"time":378293,"text":"And these immortality stories"},{"time":380092,"text":"have thousands of different manifestations,"},{"time":383089,"text":"but I believe that behind the apparent diversity"},{"time":386673,"text":"there are actually just four basic forms"},{"time":389372,"text":"that these immortality stories can take."},{"time":392883,"text":"And we can see them repeating themselves"},{"time":394688,"text":"throughout history, just with slight variations"},{"time":397858,"text":"to reflect the vocabulary of the day."},{"time":400623,"text":"Now I'm going to briefly introduce these four"},{"time":403131,"text":"basic forms of immortality story,"},{"time":405384,"text":"and I want to try to give you some sense"},{"time":406954,"text":"of the way in which they're retold by each culture"},{"time":409267,"text":"or generation"},{"time":411034,"text":"using the vocabulary of their day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413206,"text":"Now, the first story is the simplest."},{"time":415845,"text":"We want to avoid death,"},{"time":417998,"text":"and the dream of doing that in this body"},{"time":420423,"text":"in this world forever"},{"time":421783,"text":"is the first and simplest kind of immortality story,"},{"time":425074,"text":"and it might at first sound implausible,"},{"time":427533,"text":"but actually, almost every culture in human history"},{"time":431514,"text":"has had some myth or legend"},{"time":433576,"text":"of an elixir of life or a fountain of youth"},{"time":436337,"text":"or something that promises to keep us going"},{"time":439316,"text":"forever."},{"time":442453,"text":"Ancient Egypt had such myths,"},{"time":444046,"text":"ancient Babylon, ancient India."},{"time":446414,"text":"Throughout European history, we find them\nin the work of the alchemists,"},{"time":449266,"text":"and of course we still believe this today,"},{"time":452060,"text":"only we tell this story using the vocabulary"},{"time":454623,"text":"of science."},{"time":456279,"text":"So 100 years ago,"},{"time":457885,"text":"hormones had just been discovered,"},{"time":459704,"text":"and people hoped that hormone treatments"},{"time":461356,"text":"were going to cure aging and disease,"},{"time":464055,"text":"and now instead we set our hopes on stem cells,"},{"time":466908,"text":"genetic engineering, and nanotechnology."},{"time":469203,"text":"But the idea that science can cure death"},{"time":473161,"text":"is just one more chapter in the story"},{"time":475502,"text":"of the magical elixir,"},{"time":477735,"text":"a story that is as old as civilization."},{"time":482171,"text":"But betting everything on the idea of finding the elixir"},{"time":484951,"text":"and staying alive forever"},{"time":486354,"text":"is a risky strategy."},{"time":488155,"text":"When we look back through history"},{"time":490395,"text":"at all those who have sought an elixir in the past,"},{"time":493179,"text":"the one thing they now have in common"},{"time":495008,"text":"is that they're all dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497638,"text":"So we need a backup plan,\nand exactly this kind of plan B"},{"time":501376,"text":"is what the second kind of immortality story offers,"},{"time":504947,"text":"and that's resurrection."},{"time":506702,"text":"And it stays with the idea that I am this body,"},{"time":509076,"text":"I am this physical organism."},{"time":511051,"text":"It accepts that I'm going to have to die"},{"time":513219,"text":"but says, despite that,"},{"time":514593,"text":"I can rise up and I can live again."},{"time":517096,"text":"In other words, I can do what Jesus did."},{"time":519714,"text":"Jesus died, he was three days in the [tomb],"},{"time":521759,"text":"and then he rose up and lived again."},{"time":524870,"text":"And the idea that we can all be\nresurrected to live again"},{"time":527989,"text":"is orthodox believe, not just for Christians"},{"time":530277,"text":"but also Jews and Muslims."},{"time":532980,"text":"But our desire to believe this story"},{"time":535144,"text":"is so deeply embedded"},{"time":537154,"text":"that we are reinventing it again"},{"time":539252,"text":"for the scientific age,"},{"time":540744,"text":"for example, with the idea of cryonics."},{"time":543567,"text":"That's the idea that when you die,"},{"time":545157,"text":"you can have yourself frozen,"},{"time":547156,"text":"and then, at some point when technology"},{"time":549545,"text":"has advanced enough,"},{"time":550756,"text":"you can be thawed out and repaired and revived"},{"time":552876,"text":"and so resurrected."},{"time":554165,"text":"And so some people believe an omnipotent god"},{"time":557013,"text":"will resurrect them to live again,"},{"time":558892,"text":"and other people believe an \nomnipotent scientist will do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563035,"text":"But for others, the whole idea of resurrection,"},{"time":565749,"text":"of climbing out of the grave,"},{"time":567752,"text":"it's just too much like a bad zombie movie."},{"time":570471,"text":"They find the body too messy, too unreliable"},{"time":573262,"text":"to guarantee eternal life,"},{"time":575410,"text":"and so they set their hopes on the third,"},{"time":578501,"text":"more spiritual immortality story,"},{"time":580618,"text":"the idea that we can leave our body behind"},{"time":582954,"text":"and live on as a soul."},{"time":585251,"text":"Now, the majority of people on Earth"},{"time":587240,"text":"believe they have a soul,"},{"time":589013,"text":"and the idea is central to many religions."},{"time":591423,"text":"But even though, in its current form,"},{"time":593737,"text":"in its traditional form,"},{"time":595652,"text":"the idea of the soul is still hugely popular,"},{"time":597815,"text":"nonetheless we are again"},{"time":599247,"text":"reinventing it for the digital age,"},{"time":601471,"text":"for example with the idea"},{"time":602948,"text":"that you can leave your body behind"},{"time":604938,"text":"by uploading your mind, your essence,"},{"time":607184,"text":"the real you, onto a computer,"},{"time":609140,"text":"and so live on as an avatar in the ether."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613752,"text":"But of course there are skeptics who say"},{"time":615775,"text":"if we look at the evidence of science,"},{"time":617619,"text":"particularly neuroscience,"},{"time":619263,"text":"it suggests that your mind,"},{"time":621092,"text":"your essence, the real you,"},{"time":622672,"text":"is very much dependent on a particular part"},{"time":625085,"text":"of your body, that is, your brain."},{"time":627306,"text":"And such skeptics can find comfort"},{"time":629827,"text":"in the fourth kind of immortality story,"},{"time":632085,"text":"and that is legacy,"},{"time":634442,"text":"the idea that you can live on"},{"time":635922,"text":"through the echo you leave in the world,"},{"time":638173,"text":"like the great Greek warrior Achilles,"},{"time":640522,"text":"who sacrificed his life fighting at Troy"},{"time":643151,"text":"so that he might win immortal fame."},{"time":646204,"text":"And the pursuit of fame is as widespread"},{"time":648470,"text":"and popular now as it ever was,"},{"time":650611,"text":"and in our digital age,"},{"time":652190,"text":"it's even easier to achieve."},{"time":653718,"text":"You don't need to be a great warrior like Achilles"},{"time":656042,"text":"or a great king or hero."},{"time":657735,"text":"All you need is an Internet connection\nand a funny cat. (Laughter)"},{"time":662558,"text":"But some people prefer to leave a more tangible,"},{"time":665021,"text":"biological legacy -- children, for example."},{"time":667865,"text":"Or they like, they hope, to live on"},{"time":670141,"text":"as part of some greater whole,"},{"time":671858,"text":"a nation or a family or a tribe,"},{"time":674307,"text":"their gene pool."},{"time":676773,"text":"But again, there are skeptics"},{"time":678286,"text":"who doubt whether legacy"},{"time":679999,"text":"really is immortality."},{"time":681974,"text":"Woody Allen, for example, who said,"},{"time":684051,"text":"\"I don't want to live on in\nthe hearts of my countrymen."},{"time":686547,"text":"I want to live on in my apartment.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":688744,"text":"So those are the four"},{"time":690511,"text":"basic kinds of immortality stories,"},{"time":692694,"text":"and I've tried to give just some sense"},{"time":694336,"text":"of how they're retold by each generation"},{"time":696629,"text":"with just slight variations"},{"time":698216,"text":"to fit the fashions of the day."},{"time":700521,"text":"And the fact that they recur in this way,"},{"time":704010,"text":"in such a similar form but\nin such different belief systems,"},{"time":706998,"text":"suggests, I think,"},{"time":708576,"text":"that we should be skeptical of the truth"},{"time":710978,"text":"of any particular version of these stories."},{"time":714739,"text":"The fact that some people believe"},{"time":716850,"text":"an omnipotent god will resurrect them to live again"},{"time":719515,"text":"and others believe an omnipotent scientist will do it"},{"time":723216,"text":"suggests that neither are really believing this"},{"time":726254,"text":"on the strength of the evidence."},{"time":728924,"text":"Rather, we believe these stories"},{"time":731350,"text":"because we are biased to believe them,"},{"time":733333,"text":"and we are biased to believe them"},{"time":735161,"text":"because we are so afraid of death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739431,"text":"So the question is,"},{"time":741486,"text":"are we doomed to lead the one life we have"},{"time":744958,"text":"in a way that is shaped by fear and denial,"},{"time":748651,"text":"or can we overcome this bias?"},{"time":751726,"text":"Well the Greek philosopher Epicurus"},{"time":754193,"text":"thought we could."},{"time":755921,"text":"He argued that the fear of death is natural,"},{"time":759469,"text":"but it is not rational."},{"time":761884,"text":"\"Death,\" he said, \"is nothing to us,"},{"time":764542,"text":"because when we are here, death is not,"},{"time":767392,"text":"and when death is here, we are gone.\""},{"time":771145,"text":"Now this is often quoted, but it's difficult"},{"time":772943,"text":"to really grasp, to really internalize,"},{"time":775265,"text":"because exactly this idea of being gone"},{"time":777428,"text":"is so difficult to imagine."},{"time":779567,"text":"So 2,000 years later, another philosopher,"},{"time":781798,"text":"Ludwig Wittgenstein, put it like this:"},{"time":785255,"text":"\"Death is not an event in life:"},{"time":788199,"text":"We do not live to experience death."},{"time":791841,"text":"And so,\" he added,"},{"time":793035,"text":"\"in this sense, life has no end.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":795970,"text":"So it was natural for me as a child"},{"time":799146,"text":"to fear being swallowed by the void,"},{"time":801513,"text":"but it wasn't rational,"},{"time":803392,"text":"because being swallowed by the void"},{"time":805377,"text":"is not something that any of us"},{"time":807455,"text":"will ever live to experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810725,"text":"Now, overcoming this bias is not easy because"},{"time":813254,"text":"the fear of death is so deeply embedded in us,"},{"time":816213,"text":"yet when we see that the fear itself is not rational,"},{"time":820695,"text":"and when we bring out into the open"},{"time":822825,"text":"the ways in which it can unconsciously bias us,"},{"time":825523,"text":"then we can at least start"},{"time":827374,"text":"to try to minimize the influence it has"},{"time":830008,"text":"on our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831891,"text":"Now, I find it helps to see life"},{"time":834709,"text":"as being like a book:"},{"time":836553,"text":"Just as a book is bounded by its covers,"},{"time":839021,"text":"by beginning and end,"},{"time":840298,"text":"so our lives are bounded by birth and death,"},{"time":844036,"text":"and even though a book is\nlimited by beginning and end,"},{"time":847551,"text":"it can encompass distant landscapes,"},{"time":849687,"text":"exotic figures, fantastic adventures."},{"time":852917,"text":"And even though a book is\nlimited by beginning and end,"},{"time":856266,"text":"the characters within it"},{"time":858089,"text":"know no horizons."},{"time":860931,"text":"They only know the moments\nthat make up their story,"},{"time":864088,"text":"even when the book is closed."},{"time":867028,"text":"And so the characters of a book"},{"time":869164,"text":"are not afraid of reaching the last page."},{"time":872646,"text":"Long John Silver is not afraid of you"},{"time":874924,"text":"finishing your copy of \"Treasure Island.\""},{"time":877759,"text":"And so it should be with us."},{"time":879459,"text":"Imagine the book of your life,"},{"time":881603,"text":"its covers, its beginning and end,\nand your birth and your death."},{"time":884387,"text":"You can only know the moments in between,"},{"time":886564,"text":"the moments that make up your life."},{"time":888499,"text":"It makes no sense for you to fear"},{"time":890446,"text":"what is outside of those covers,"},{"time":892536,"text":"whether before your birth"},{"time":894006,"text":"or after your death."},{"time":895982,"text":"And you needn't worry how long the book is,"},{"time":898511,"text":"or whether it's a comic strip or an epic."},{"time":901984,"text":"The only thing that matters"},{"time":903526,"text":"is that you make it a good story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907024,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909244,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}